subSubSection.paragraph:
According to the original description, «posterior margin of terga ... IV–X with stout pointed triangular teeth arranged into a simple row» (
Soldán et al . 1987: 346
); however, in the holotype tergum IV has no denticles (teeth), and the denticles are present beginning from the tergum V ( Fig. 682 ). Structure of tergum X was not reported in the original description; the holotype has one pair of large denticles on angles of its posterior projection ( Fig. 683 ).
